{
  "texts": [
    "We believe these aspects of our work suggest a promising area for future research.",
    "Prompt, Adapter and Low-rank techniques introduce extra parameters for training, which may potentially extend training duration and/or memory footprint in comparison to selective methods.",
    "However, they have the advantage of being more flexible and are often easier to use.",
    "Prefix and Adapter methods result in extra parameters after adaptation, potentially increasing inference time and memory footprint relative to the vanilla model.",
    "Conversely, LoRA merges newly trained low-rank matrices with the original frozen ones, eliminating additional parameters at inference."
  ]
}